 to track client milestones beyond birthdays. Contract renewal dates, follow-up deadlines, and project anniversaries all deserve tracking. TinyContacts handles these varied date types without forcing everything into a \"birthday\" field, supporting nuanced professional relationship management. Conference and networking event attendees face the perennial challenge of capturing new contacts quickly and adding context before memories fade. The notes field (planned feature) captures \"met at TechConf 2025, interested in API integrations\" context that makes follow-up meaningful and personal. The search functionality quickly answers questions like \"who do I know at Stanford working on machine learning?\" Event organizers manage diverse contact types - vendors, venues, speakers, sponsors, attendees - each requiring different information. TinyContacts' flexible data model accommodates these varied needs without forcing everyone into the same rigid template. Writers and journalists maintain source contact lists where context and relationship history matter enormously. TinyContacts provides a reliable system for organizing sources by beat, expertise, or publication, ensuring the right contacts are accessible when deadlines loom. Real estate agents, insurance brokers, and other relationship-driven professionals manage hundreds of client contacts where small personal touches matter. Remembering a client's preferred communication method, family member names, or important dates strengthens relationships and builds loyalty. Having a comprehensive, organized contact database improves response times to inquiries, demonstrates professionalism, and prevents the embarrassment of forgetting who people are or how you know them. Client contact information remains under the professional's control rather than residing in cloud services with uncertain data handling practices. Clients requesting their data receive complete, formatted exports without manual compilation efforts. While professional benefits are substantial, TinyContacts equally enhances personal life by supporting meaningful relationships through better organization and memory assistance. The birthday and anniversary tracking features prevent missed important dates that can damage relationships. Users track relationships, important dates for numerous relatives, and contact information for family members dispersed geographically. Friend groups from different life contexts (college, work, hobbies, neighborhood) organize easily with tagging. Couples managing shared social networks benefit from TinyContacts' multi-user capabilities (planned). Setting reminders to \"call mom weekly\" or \"check in with college roommate monthly\" helps maintain connections despite geographic separation and busy schedules. Screen reader compatibility enables visually impaired users to manage contacts independently. Semantic HTML, ARIA labels, and logical focus management ensure assistive technologies convey complete interface state and functionality. All functionality is accessible without a mouse, with visible focus indicators showing current position. Consistent interaction patterns reduce learning burden for users with cognitive impairments or memory challenges. Error prevention through validation and confirmation dialogs protects users prone to mistakes from data loss or unintended actions. Touch-friendly targets on mobile devices accommodate users with motor control challenges or larger fingers. Adequate spacing between interactive elements prevents accidental activation of adjacent controls. In an era of increasing surveillance and data exploitation, TinyContacts' privacy-first architecture delivers peace of mind and practical security. Local data storage means contact information never leaves the user's device without explicit action. The application functions completely offline after initial load, ensuring access to contacts regardless of internet connectivity. Flights, rural areas, or network outages d